rlCli.description: Remote CLI branch has been added.

rlCliMibVersion.name: rlCliMibVersion
rlCliMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 3.

rlCLIremoteCLIcommand.name: rlCLIremoteCLIcommand
rlCLIremoteCLIcommand.description: Commands that can be given for execution of CLI from remote: takeRemoteCLI: take resources of remote CLI activation releaseRemoteCLI: free resources of remote CLI activation applySentCLI: apply the CLI commands that are currently in rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsTable. deleteCommandsCLI: delete all the CLI commands that are currently in rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsTable. setEchoModeCLI: entered commands will appear before its output in rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsTable. unsetEchoModeCLI: entered commands will not appear in rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsTable.

rlCLIremoteCLIexecutionState.name: rlCLIremoteCLIexecutionState
rlCLIremoteCLIexecutionState.description: The execution state of remote CLI: notActive: no 'applySentCLI' command has been given. This is the default state. The remote CLI reverts to this state each time when the 1st entry is added to rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsTable. inProcess: Executing commands - no output available outputAvailable: Some output is already available, although the commands execution may not be finished yet. waitingForOutputRetrieval: The rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsTable is full and remote CLI is waiting for the manager to retrieve the output. done: All the commands in rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsTable have been executed.

rlCLIremoteCLIexecutionCommandIndex.name: rlCLIremoteCLIexecutionCommandIndex
rlCLIremoteCLIexecutionCommandIndex.description: Index of command, which is currently in execution. 0 if none.

rlCLIremoteCLImode.name: rlCLIremoteCLImode
rlCLIremoteCLImode.description: Operation mode of remote CLI: deleteCLIOutputOnGet: output row will be deleted after GET. Recommended for reliable management channels. keepCLIOutputOnGet: output row will be kept after GET, will be deleted only explicitly by remote CLI client or upon release of remote CLI resources. Recommended for non-reliable management channels.

rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsTable.name: rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsTable
rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsTable.description: A list of CLI commands to execute.

rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsEntry.name: rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsEntry
rlCLIremoteCLIcommandsEntry.description: An entry containing a part of a CLI command.

rlCLIremoteCLIcommandIndex.name: rlCLIremoteCLIcommandIndex
rlCLIremoteCLIcommandIndex.description: The index of the command. The commands will be executed in order of their indexes.

rlCLIremoteCLIcommandPartNumber.name: rlCLIremoteCLIcommandPartNumber
rlCLIremoteCLIcommandPartNumber.description: The part of the command. Long commands will be divided in several parts, which will be concatenated before execution.

rlCLIremoteCLIcommandPart.name: rlCLIremoteCLIcommandPart
rlCLIremoteCLIcommandPart.description: The text of the command part.

rlCLIremoteCLIactivationStatus.name: rlCLIremoteCLIactivationStatus
rlCLIremoteCLIactivationStatus.description: Activation status of the command. Any value greater than 0 indicates that the command has been activated and failed

rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsTable.name: rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsTable
rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsTable.description: A list of CLI output rows.

rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsEntry.name: rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsEntry
rlCLIremoteCLIoutputsEntry.description: An entry containing a part of a CLI output row.

rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowIndex.name: rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowIndex
rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowIndex.description: The index of the output row.

rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowPartNumber.name: rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowPartNumber
rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowPartNumber.description: The part of the output row.

rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowPart.name: rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowPart
rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowPart.description: The text of the output row part.

rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowStatus.name: rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowStatus
rlCLIremoteCLIoutputRowStatus.description: The status of the command part. Only destroy will be accepted as value for SET.

rlCLIremoteCLIoutputCommandNumber.name: rlCLIremoteCLIoutputCommandNumber
rlCLIremoteCLIoutputCommandNumber.description: The command index of the command whose activation generated thist output row.

rlCLIremoteCLIinstance.name: rlCLIremoteCLIinstance
rlCLIremoteCLIinstance.description: The remote CLI instance. A value of 0xFFFFFFFF indicates that no instance corresponding to the client was found.
